stories.title: Pakistan v India
stories.subTitle: Fifth One-Day International
stories.summary: Finally, a game that was over long before it was over. For the fifth time, Inzamam-ul-Haq won the toss; for the third time, he put India in.

stories.title: India feted, a Pakistani great snubbed
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 5th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: Whoever thought Pakistan might feel like Sharjah, with thousands of Indians cheering, shouting and blaring horns in support of their team
stories.byline: Roving Reporter by Anand Vasu in Lahore

stories.title: Fighting till the last ball
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 5th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: Post-match quotes from Sourav Ganguly, Inzamam-ul-Haq and VVS Laxman

stories.title: Laxman and Pathan star in emphatic Indian win
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 5th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: VVS Laxman scored a glorious 107, while Irfan Pathan struck three crucial blows with the new ball, as India won the final match by 40 runs to clinch the five-match series 3-2
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by S Rajesh
